"Best of Both Worlds - Revisiting the Spymasters Double Agent Problem.","2","2. In the ‘Initialize shared state’ phase, SimC, on behalf of each honest party Pi′ ̸∈Z, samples a random input xi′ ←{0, 1} and creates shares {[xi′]i}i∈[n] ←Sharen,n(xi′). For each i′ ∈[n], it creates shares also of the randomnesses {[ri′]i}i∈[n] ←Sharen,n(ri′). It sends the set of shares {[xi′]i, [ri′]i}Pi′̸∈Z to the corrupt party Pi ∈Z."
"Best of Both Worlds - Revisiting the Spymasters Double Agent Problem.","2","3. For each virtual party Vi ∈V and each round j ∈[r] of the virtual protocol Πstat, for the protocol ΠNxtMsgj i as in Figure 4, SimC makes a black-box call to the PPT simulator Sim NxtMsgj i C that can simulate the view of the corrupt parties in a way that is computationally indistinguishable from the real view. Let this set of views be, { ˆ View Z NxtMsgj i }i∈[n],j∈[r]"
