"Cloning Games: A General Framework for Unclonable Primitives.","2","[CLLZ21]. 84 Next, we will analyze the evolution of the state shared by B′ and C′ step by step. Since the actions of B′ and C′ commute, we can synchronously track their operations. After the ﬁrst step, the state is given by  U kB B ⊗U kC C  1 |R| X r,r′∈R |r⟩B |r′⟩C |ϕk,x⟩BC = 1 |R| X r,r′∈R |r⟩B |r′⟩C |Γk,x,r,r′⟩. Next, B′ and C′ each apply a Z gate to their register storing the inner product, which results in the state 1 |R| X r,r′∈R |r⟩B |r′⟩C (−1)⟨r,x⟩⊕⟨r′,x⟩  αk,x,r,r′ |⟨r, x⟩⟩B |⟨r′, x⟩⟩C |φ0 k,x,r,r′⟩BC −βk,x,r,r′ |⟨r, x⟩⟩B |⟨r′, x⟩⟩C |φ1 k,x,r,r′⟩BC −θk,x,r,r′ |⟨r, x⟩⟩B |⟨r′, x⟩⟩C |φ2 k,x,r,r′⟩BC + γk,x,r,r′ |⟨r, x⟩⟩B |⟨r′, x⟩⟩C |φ3 k,x,r,r′⟩BC  =: 1 |R| X r,r′∈R |r⟩B |r′⟩C |Γ′ k,x,r,r′⟩, with ⟨Γk,x,r,r′, Γ′ k,x,r,r′⟩= (−1)⟨r,x⟩⊕⟨r′,x⟩␀|αk,x,r|2 −|βk,x,r|2 −|θk,x,r|2 + |γk,x,r|2 . Now B′ and C′ uncompute the unitary U kB B ⊗U kC C , and the state becomes  U kB B ⊗U kC C † 1 |R| X r∈R |r⟩B |r′⟩C |Γ′ k,x,r,r′⟩= 1 |R| X r∈R |r⟩B |r′⟩C  U kB,r B ⊗U kC,r′ C † |Γ′ k,x,r,r′⟩ = 1 |R| X r,r′∈R |r⟩B |r′⟩C  (−1)⟨r,x⟩⊕⟨r′,x⟩␀|αk,x,r,r′|2 −|βk,x,r,r′|2 −|θk,x,r,r′|2 + |γk,x,r,r′|2 |ϕk,x⟩BC + |errk,x,r,r′⟩  , where |errk,x,r,r′⟩is a subnormalized state orthogonal to |ϕk,x⟩BC. Next, B′ and C′ each apply a Quantum Fourier Transform (QFT) on their random coins, resulting in the state 1 |R|2 X r,r′∈R X y,z∈R (−1)⟨r,y⟩⊕⟨r′,z⟩|y⟩B |z⟩C  (−1)⟨r,x⟩⊕⟨r′,x⟩␀|αk,x,r,r′|2 −|βk,x,r,r′|2 −|θk,x,r,r′|2 + |γk,x,r,r′|2 |ϕk,x⟩BC + |errk,x,r,r′⟩  . Note that the coeﬃcient of |x⟩B |x⟩C |ϕk,x⟩equals 1 |R|2 X r,r′∈R |αk,x,r,r′|2 −|βk,x,r,r′|2 −|θk,x,r,r′|2 + |γk,x,r,r′|2, 85 so the probability that B′ and C′ both output x is lower bounded by Pr [y = z = x] ≥E k,x 1 |R|2 X r,r′∈R |αk,x,r,r′|2 −|βk,x,r,r′|2 −|θk,x,r,r′|2 + |γk,x,r,r′|2 2 = E k,x E r,r′ |αk,x,r,r′|2 −|βk,x,r,r′|2 −|θk,x,r,r′|2 + |γk,x,r,r′|2 2 ≥ E k,x,r,r′ |αk,x,r,r′|2 −|βk,x,r,r′|2 −|θk,x,r,r′|2 + |γk,x,r,r′|2 2 ≥4ε2, where we used Cauchy-Schwartz Inequality and eq. (19). 86"
